column2: Partly sunny- calm- water milky/cloudy past week.
Clear- light wind- very light boat activity.
Finally stopped raining so could take reading.
Major fly hatch past week- people taking in piers and boats.
Floating/suspended globs of red/brown material last week- evenly dispersed today.
Pretty quiet with all the tourists gone- lake has not cleared up.
Ice went out 4-7. Loons are on the lake.
Sun finally came out. Clear blue sky- no wind.
Many large "globs" of light green algae have developed over the past few weeks.
A little rough out today- but nice and sunny.
Beautiful day-finally- loon on lake this week-strange- a few cases of swimmers itch on east shore.
The lake has been quiet all summer- rain last couple of days May have affected the water density.
Algae bloom this week kept a lot of people out of the water.
Water is down- need some rain.
No change from last couple of weeks.  Back to work Monday- its been a great "summer" !
Lake is improving somewhat.  Lots of people taking out boats- rafts and piers.
Rain equals 6+ " this week- brought the lake up to the April and May level.
Great day- water is much improved...lots of minnows out in the middle of the lake.
What a beautiful day.  Went goose hunting- went fishing ...
Great fall day- geese flying- quiet and peaceful!
This May be the last reading this year- my boat is the last on the lake- will have to come out soon.
That's all folks- see you next year.  Pier comes out next week.
Ice went out 4-23-93- the lake is stirred up now.  I saw a mute or whistling swan on the lake yesterday.
Lake looks a little nasty- but it's a beautiful day. The lake level is up to the bottom of the pier- very high.
Crappie and trout biting- frost last night- Memorial Weekend quiet.
Big storms and rain yesterday/last night.  May have kicked up lake a bit.  Lots of hail- windy today but the sun came out a bit for me to do the sampling.
Additional 4" of rain- pier almost under water.
Used my fish locator to ensure I was at deepest point and to avoid hitting bottom with sampler.
Beautiful day- clear- blue sky- no wind.
Water like glass- sandhill cranes flying south.
Lake association meeting today.  May be elected to be the big pres.  Lots of boating expected this weekend.
No news- real quiet- lots of rafts- piers and boats out of water.
First day of fall- beautiful!  lots of geese flying!
What a fantastic day- bluebird colors at their peak.
Ice off 4-7- suckers spawning on beach- I think turnover is in progress.
My partner and I took 1st place (3rd in 6 years) on the 6th annual wool lake fishing invitational.
Clear- calm- beautiful day.  Rainbow trout for dinner tonight.
Sun came out just long enough.  Big weekend and assoc. meeting coming up.
A lot less boat traffic this year- much less rain too.  Lake down a couple of inches.  People asking about all that "green stuff".  Still nicer than many lakes I've seen.
Temps. in the 90's last couple weeks- high humidity- need rain.
Some people complaining about "green stuff" on beach.
Rain this week.  Raised lake level 2+"s.  First great American Secchi Dip In reading.
Rain for this week was 8 inches- lake is up 3-4 inches.  Algae bloom appears to be over.
Cool- cloudy and rain all last week.  Summer is over   back to the real world (work) tomorrow.
Big storms last night.  Nearly 2" of rain.
Piers + boats coming out.  Summer over
Hot (80's) - humid all week- great weather.
I was at the end of my rope + still could see (response sent) .
Cloudy today- secchi reading is approximate- could not do one today.  60's in the last few days- last reading
Ice off 3/27/95.  Loon on the lake- will be gone as soon as traffic picks up.
Suckers spawned on beach 2 weeks ago.  Loons gone.  7th annual wood lake fishing international this weekend.
Been fishing this lake for almost 20 years + just caught a stripper bass.
Department of Natural Resources netting fish today.
Summer's finally here.  High in 80's.  Lots of pollen on lake surface.
Clear- breezy- very nice- air temp is 65 degrees.  It was pretty windy before we finished.
90's all last week + this week too!  More algae than "normal".
Lake clearing up nicely- big weekend coming up 3+" of rain this week.
This reading was sent in to 2nd annual great American Secchi Dip-In.
Water is down from last year- 90's temp again this week.
This goes with yesterday's TSI reading.
Quite a bit of reddish brown algae floating- suspended and washing up on beach.
Happy Halloween!  Pier comes out this weekend.
Ice out this year on April 19.
This is our reading for the great 1996 Dip-In.
Several cases of swimmers itch in the last couple of weeks.
Quite a bit of red-brown algae floating and suspended.  Otherwise- pretty nice.
Hot humid-no rain for 10-14 days.  Lots of piers came out yesterday.  More ducks on lake than usual.
Ice out 4-6-97.  Loons on lake- piers going in.
Mature bald eagle circled lake 2 weeks ago.  Suckers spawning on beach 4-26- now thousands of minnows around.  Ice off April 6.
Low morning temperature last week was 28 degrees.  This week clear skies and 80 degrees.
A few reports of swimmers itch.
Still some swimmers itch.  Great American Secchi Dip-In this time.  How's the 800 line coming
Few more cases of swimmers itch.
A few cases of swimmers itch.
Ducks + loons on lake.  28 F this morning.  Ice out 3-31-99
5-6" of rain this week.  Only have 1 bottle for D.O. test.
Trout released 2 weeks ago.  Osprey eating them.
DEEP SPOT - BASELINE LAKES SPRING PROTOCOL
2 Osprey flying over the lake.  Clear weather. The lake water was stunning.
cloudy and light wind.  My wife Anne Duffy helped with this report.
